    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The habit, power, state, or faculty of being able to locate, gain entry to, and use something, such as a building or a database. In computer-based information retrieval, access is the method by which a computer refers to records in a file, dependent upon their arrangement.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
